values:
im just so freaking happy right now.
i have no drama in my life.
I just had the best spring break ever. 
Imagine 9 girls going on a trip together.
You would think drama but we didnt have any problems.
I cant name all the hilarous things that happened.
This trip was a reminder just how awesome my friends are and
how truly lucky i am to have found this group.
Throughout all of the shitty things that have been thrown
at us this year we have gotten through it together.
i dont mean to sound conceded or a Kno-It-All
but i really cant think of this big of a group of girls that 
know as much or are as close as we are.
I just cant believe all the times this year that i have been
upset or worried about boys.
key word... boys.
who gives a fuck.
i have friends
what more do i need.
nothing

ive really been trying to make a effort to be nicer.
its hard granted when i always run my mouth and speak before
i think but im really trying. its going to be awkward to see
the ex boyfriends from prom but ill be with my friends and hopefully
i can ignore them and have the best night i can
thank you girls for everything

things were going alright
the friends thing was working out
god why do i have to be such a old fashioned girl

i hate it

and it just be awesome like it always is when we are alone or when we talk
why cant i just accept that im not going to have ur attention 247






And if that boy drove through the night to see me its got to me he likes me somewhat right?
idk whats the deal but im enjoying getting to know him

One Down.
One to go.
Funeral tomorrow.
Its going to be the worst day so far i think.
Seeing Tyler laying down not smiling, not jumping around
like his usually ADHD self was so hard to take. 
Whats even harder is that Austin, who im really not that close to
gave me this huge hug and told me that Katee needed me and to
take care of her and to be strong.
Im so glad that we have a huge support system... like all the girls
so its not like its all up to me to help katee. We are all there.
And i think she knows that she can call anyone of us.
I know that i feel like its my job to bare the burden of it all.
But i cant blame myself.
I know deep down it wasnt me and Katees fault. Tyler wasnt
meant to come to Lafayette with us.
I hope Katee knows that too.  She does.
I hope that we can bring her comfort because theres such
a long way to go for her to heal.
To think its only been 2 full days since.... it.
seems like its been a lifetime.
For a moment we will all be laughin like old times
but them we remember why we are together.
And then we will laugh about Tyler and all the silly things he did.
He did many of them.
I hope we can one day just talk about him without crying.

All i can do it smile.
He makes me feel so different.
Like this talking this is so different from what its normally like.
For instance i hate talking on the phone.
But with him we will talk for like 3 hours and i wont even seem like it.  THREE hours people.  Thats something i have never done.
Idk. I mean its not like we have everything in common. We are pretty
different. But i just dont know. It just feels right. Its not like
oh i want to get in his pants or all i want to do is kiss him.
Its just like. I want to talk to him. I want to know what he thinks on everything. I cant explain it.
: )
Why is it that i want what i cant have? But its not that i want it because i cant have it.  Ive always wanted it.  But now im reminded of it all the time.  I just cant win.

I may have cried yesterday but i didnt call!
And i know that seems pathetic but for me its quite an accomplishment.
Why make someone a priority who only makes you an option?

Im so thankful for them.  Jenny has been checking up on me and been putting up with my crying.  I appreciate all she has been doing.  I hope you read this and know how much it means to me. Im in such an unexplainable state right now.
Its one thats kind of content, thankful, and relaxed. But those words realy dont completely
describe it either.  Its amazing how something i thought would be so drama filled would help
me so much. I just feel that i bonded with so many different people.  Even my friends that i couldnt
learn anything new about i did.  I really wish everyone could have gotten as much out of retreat
as i did.  Im not sure if i got closer to God on this retreat but i got closer to everyone
and learned alot about myself so i guess that is Godlike?? I apologized to some people that i really
owed an apology to and you know they accepted them without hesitation.  Its so amazing to me.
I have so much respect for these people because i know that i dont deserve their acceptance and their
understanding but they have given it to me without any questions.  It makes me feel so bad that i hold
grudges against people. I know now that i honestly do.  Im trying to work on it.  I fixed two of them
that i had this weekend and it feels like so much weight has been lifted off me.  I know that theres alot
of people that i want to talk to so i can get closure on some things but i know i cant.  But just
knowing that the people i AM able to work things out with have accepted me in just unreal.
Im going to take this as a lesson in that if they can forgive me i can forgive others.
I really hope that i can keep this state of mind and that it wasnt just the retreat atomsphere.
i almost beat a fucking bitch down.

i ache.
Everywhere.
I never knew it was possible to feel this bad.  I havent eaten in 3
days.  I no longer know what its like to consume food.  Spirte has become my only
source of nutrition.  The bathroom has become my best friend and where i spend most of my time.
Honestly, why does God hate me? This whole sick thing is starting to become ridiculous.
It bothers me cause my friends are like why are you never at school and you never do anything anymore
and it really just hurts my feelings.  Its like people think i honestly like missing school. i would
give anything to just have 3 or 4 weeks go by where i dont get a miagraine, fever, or throwup.
I have NEVER had fever before but now its like a familiar place since i have gotten in so much lately.
i dont know whats wrong with me.  I dont have anemia and they said my blood pressure is low.
But what does that exactly mean? They are like drink more things with salt? Wow thanks
its like seriously you people have spent YEARS in medical school and ur tryng to tell me that
theres nothing you can do? Honestly its getting a little old.  Why cant they just prescribe me
every medicene known to man with a list of symptons so if i feel it i can take it.  Ive gone to the doctor
twice in the past 2 weeks.  We spend so much money on all the drugs i have to take.  I feel so bad
but theres NOTHING i can do about it.  I feel so out of contact with the rest of the world.
The only thing i know is the feel of my bed.

YAY for friends
yay for making new ones and new memories
I may not like any boys right now.  Like seriously none.  I am the most
boy crazy person you will meet but for now all thats on my mind is the fun
times that im having with the girls the last year of highschool.  Its really sad
and i was thinking that after this year things might be different.  Like i know in college
things change, people change, and grow apart but why cant we all stay in touch? It sucks
because its taken me sooo long to finally find a group where i feel myself and fit in and now
it just a little less than a year we will all be in different places.  Not all of us.  But im
definately going to be seperated because NO ONE is going to ULL.  I really dont know what im going to
do.  Its a scary thought being on my own with no one with me.  Like today what started off
as a hello email became this 7535845 email extravaganza complete with pictures of boys and
girls that i hope my friends dont become attached too.  It was hilarous and all of us laughed
in our class periods.  I want that next year. :(

this weekend is going to be so much fun!
im really excited.
everything has been going really great lately!

It was good to catch up.

fuck

tonight ill be dreaming of you.
wondering where you are

Last night totally rocked
Like seriously
i dont know about everyone else but usually Catholic dances tend
to bite.  I really havent been to any since freshman year.
I had a feeling this would be a good one just because we got to dress up
and we are seniors and so we have the right to act totally stupid.
Im so glad that we all went together because the more people made it fun.
There wasnt much of a football game but i did catch a pass lol.
Then there was the surprise attack. I have to say Seniors yall handled
it awesome even I was taken offguard.  Everyone was soaked but it
was time for the slip in slide. Im so freaking excited about the pictures lol.
We took some good group pictures like us all wet and soapy, everyone before at Canes,
everyone at Mallorys, the backs of our shirts, ect. ect.
Then there was Chubby bunny.  Katee put 13 in her mouth, thats extrodinary.
Im kinda of scared to see those pictures, the ones of people spitting out white stuff....
I liked when we all went in that guess room and we sat and talked. It was kind of rowdy
because soooooo many people in one room all wanting to talk. I think for the most part
we kept it under control??? Im glad that i got to learn all the other freshmans names.
We really have a great group of them.  We have some that are quiet but they all pretty
much participated in everything.  I hope that they had a good time cause i had a BLAST. 
I just want to say through all teh drama you can have with a BIG group of girls i want yall
to know that i love and appreciate everyone of you and im so thankful to have such a
diverse and fun group of girls.  I couldnt ask for better friends.  Im so happy this
year because i feel that i am getting closer to the girls in our big group that i didnt
know well. I dont mean to get all feeling and blah like.  Its just someone mentioned 
you know its the last time we have a back
to school dance and its really sad.  I think the whole senioritis thing they are talking about
is kicking in.

Tomarrow is the first day of the last year of my highschool career.
Needless to say i have feelings of excitment, nervousness, and regret.
It sucks that it is almost all over and i still feel that i havent done everything i need to.
All i know is that every oportunity that comes to me this year im going to take.
And boys right now... The last guy i wrote about i had a long talk with and i told him where i stand
that he has to do the college thing and i the senior thing for now.  Im not sure what this means
for us in the future but i know for now that it wouldnt work because he needs to be single
and i need to be with my friends and live it up.
Im trying everything to make this year perfect.
Im going to go back on my diet plan ( AMEN! lol)
Im going to try to be nice to everyone and not gossip ( gosh it will be hard lol)
And try to confront and talk to people that i may have not before.
Im just sooo excited!

sugar while watching " Are you Afarid of the Dark" like every Friday?
When did we all grow up and leave our childhood?

I feel like there is no need for conversation
Some questions are better left without a reason
And I would rather reveal myself than my situation
Now and then I consider, my hesitation

The more the light shines through me
I pretend to close my eyes
The more the dark consumes me
I pretend I'm burning, burning bright

I wonder if the things I did were just to be different
To spare myself of the constant shame of my existence
And I would surely redeem myself in my desperation
Here and now I'll express, my situation

There's nothing ever wrong but nothing's ever right
Such a cruel contradiction
I know I cross the lines its not easy to define
I'm born to indecision
There's always something new some path I'm supposed to choose
With no particular rhyme or reason

The more the light shines through me
I pretend to close my eyes
The more the dark consumes me
I pretend I'm burning, burning bright

Well this morning me and danielle left jennys at 8:30
i came home and slept and JUST woke up... that should tell you
we had an AWESOME NIGHT
so heres how the night went...

Chad came pick me up he looked soooooo cute he had suspenders
and everything! Then we went to Jennys and were the FIRST people there
( i should have known my friends always arrive fashionable late lol)
FINALLY everyone else got there and we took like 2748348357 pictures!
I finally got to see Lees dress she was raving about and it was sooo pretty!
We all went to meet Katee, Charles, Laura, Donny, Erin, Jordan, Sarah, Steven,
Mary, and Teresa at Carrabas but since we were an HOUR late they didnt have a table
and the wait was too long so of course Jenny to the rescue! Mr. Don had a table
all nice and ready in a private room when we got there! Dinner was so much fun
and the food was FANTASTIC! I feel so guilty because Mr. Don payed for it all.
The dance was fun seeing everyone and seeing who went with who but the music
was honestly not that good. It was hard to dance to and the songs were so old
i didnt even know what they were! It took like 30 minutes to take pictures.
We took a group one with all the girls! There was 9 of us so i HOPE it came out
cute!!!! We left the dance around 11:30 and went back to Jennys to change then went
to tina's. They had so many random people there but all really nice girls and guys.
I saw 2 guys that i hadnt seen in forever! 1 i use to be in love with in like 8th grade
and the other guy i was mad at for a reason. I talked to both of them for awhile and realized
1. the 8th grade crush is still very very cute and still the same personality( wowwwwwwwwwwww)
2. The other guy i had been mad at had nothing to do with a particular event so i really had
been mad at him for no reason. Its funny how things can be miscomunicated.
Well after we left Tina's we went back to Jennys at like 4 and talked about tonight and watched " Meet the
Fockers" but everyone was like passed out before we were into the movie about 30 minutes.
Of course i was the last one to fall asleep.

Well thats pretty much how the night went! Everyone was great and we didnt have any drama! YAY!
Im looking forward to next years!
